Section section_01 (Chars 0–7852):
Section Summary: The narrator's friend, George Corvick, asks him to write a review of Hugh Vereker's new novel for the periodical "The Middle". Corvick is unable to write the review himself as he has to rush to Paris to be with his friend Gwendolen Erme, whose mother is ill. The narrator writes the review, but later worries that it may not have done justice to Vereker's work, especially after Corvick implies that he should have delved deeper into the author's meaning. The narrator meets Vereker at a social gathering, but doesn't get a chance to discuss his review with him, although Lady Jane eventually brings it up and praises the narrator's writing. The narrator is relieved that Lady Jane has spoken up, as it saves him from having to awkwardly bring up the topic himself.
