Section section_02 (Chars 7852–11221):
Section Summary: Lady Jane is excited to show a review of Hugh Vereker's work to him, and she has marked the passages that she particularly likes. When the author of the review reveals himself to Lady Jane, she seems less impressed, as if the article's value is diminished by the fact that it was written by someone she knows. At dinner, the author waits to see how Vereker will react to the review, but Vereker dismisses it as "the usual twaddle" when asked about it by another guest, Miss Poyle. Vereker's response surprises the author, who had expected him to be pleased by the praise. Vereker's comments suggest that he does not take the review seriously and may even find it superficial.
